   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Thirty-seven THOSE WHO CHOOSE ANOTHER GOD Scripture: Psa 16:4</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>This is to explain the difference between the true God and false gods.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>There is a God in the universe: there must be a God in the universe There is only one God God s name is JEHOVAH</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Explain the meaning of the name Jehovah.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God is the I AM.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>God is the One Who is, and Who was, and Who is to come Rev 1:4 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>All other gods are not God</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Explain this point clearly with abundant materials to prove the point.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Those who choose another god Those who choose another god worship idols.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The result of idol worship is the multiplication of sorrows.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Use a lot of examples to describe the sorrowful conditions of the people who worship idols.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Cast off idols and return to God Explain that men should worship the Lord of the heavens and the earth.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>This Lord of the heavens and the earth became flesh, and His name is Jesus Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Today, if a man returns to God, he must return to the Lord Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>How to turn to the Lord Sin separates man from God and leads him to go astray to worship false gods.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Therefore, man must confess his sins and repent.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>He must accept the redemption of Jesus Christ and receive Him as the Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>He must destroy the idols.</S>
   </TEXT>
